dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons b Naved-ul-Hasan 70 (130b 7x4 0x6 192m) SR: 53.84

dismissalComment.html: Crash! Simmons backs up even before the release, Naved pings the blockhole and bang. The furniture is disturbed. Simmons was trying to drive square on the off side. A very good innings from the youngster.

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle lbw b Naved-ul-Hasan 41 (37b 7x4 1x6 41m) SR: 110.81

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels c Imran Farhat b Iftikhar Anjum 13 (20b 1x4 0x6 30m) SR: 65

dismissalComment.html: and gone! 43 required off 59 balls and Farhat swings his bat around as if they require 430 off 59 balls - ball clips the top edge and balloons up towards long-off. Samuels moves in from the deep and nicely settles under it.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Taylor b Gayle 31 (43b 2x4 1x6 60m) SR: 72.09

dismissalComment.html: what a catch! Tossed up on middle and off, Hafeez again goes down and tries the slog-sweep, not timed as well as the previous attempts, ends up slamming it high down towards a very wide long-on, looks like its going for maximum but Taylor times his jump to perfection and pouches it above his head, great stuff and Gayle gets the breakthrough

headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Rehman player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: all over! good length delivery, pitched in line and angling across. Malik stands tall and drives hard, ball clips the inside edge and races away to the vacant fine leg fence - Pakistan win by 7 wickets.

commentPostTextItems.html: Handshakes all around as the players walk back to the pavilion. It's party time in the stands.

Hafeez and Farhat added 64 runs for the first wicket and that set the platform. Farhat was the top scorer on 58, an innings which can be at best described as streaky. West Indies bowlers were an indisciplined lot today, in all they conceded 31 extras and made life easy for the batsmen. Their fielding too was sloppy and couple of chances that could have turned this match around were grassed. Pakistan batsmen took full advantage of the friendly approach and they reached the target with 8 balls remaining.

Pakistan now lead the 5-ODI series with two more matches left to be played, so it's an unassailable lead and from what we have seen so far, a West Indian comeback looks remote. That's it from me Sajan Nair and Jamie Alter - The 4th ODI is on the 13th of December, so dress scary -  Good night and good luck.

commentTextItems.html: pushed away towards cover and they scamper through for a single
short of a good length delivery, hint of swing and Yousuf is beaten on the forward prod
game, set and match! good length delivery outside the off stump. Yousuf gets a good stride in towards the line of the ball and square drives it point. what a player
turned away towards midwicket - no room for a single there

commentTextItems.html: flatter delivery outside the off stump and Yousuf punches it well wide of the fielder at cover - Pakistan inch closer
worked away well wide of the fielder at short fine leg
tossed up outside the off stump, Yousuf goes low down and paddles it down to fine leg for a single - it's looking all to easy at the moment
another wide, so what's new? again way down the leg side and Ramdin fails to collect it cleanly

commentPreTextItems.html: Gayle back on, probably the last roll of the dice from Lara

commentTextItems.html: comes down the track and works it away towards midwicket, awkward looking shot and the ball beats the diving fielder at short midwicket
pitched up and Yousuf drives it straight back down the track. Bradshaw moves across to his left and the half-stop cuts off a single

commentPostTextItems.html: Pakistan require another 14 runs with 7 wickets and 18 balls remaining.

commentTextItems.html: angled away behind point. Smith moves across quickly and cuts off the single
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line. Malik pushes forward and thuds it down to long-on for a single. Presented the full face of the bat there
short and angling across - swing and a miss outside the off stump
again drifting down the leg side. wrong line and length from Bradshaw, Malik fails to make contact but the ball clips the pad and runs down to third man
short and angling across the right-hander. Yousuf stands his ground and steers it down to third man. Made it look easy
oh dear! good length delivery, drifting down the leg side and that's another wide
good length delivery outside the off stump and Malik jabs it through extra cover for a brace - deliberately hit in the air and he placed it to perfection

dismissalText.commentary: Runako Morton b Abdur Rehman 7 (17b 0x4 0x6 16m) SR: 41.17

dismissalComment.html: Morton departs, done in by the arm ball - pitched on and around the middle and off stump line and this one went straight on at a fairly decent pace. Morton goes back and plays across the line - turned out to be a notting shot in the end and the off stump is pegged back

headshotImage.longCaption: Umar Gul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Smith b Umar Gul 23 (30b 2x4 1x6 25m) SR: 76.66

dismissalComment.html: bowled'm! yorker on the middle and leg stump line  - hint of reversing and Smith plays all over it -  leg stumps goes for a walk. Gul gets his revenge, West Indies 6 down.

dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons b Naved-ul-Hasan 70 (130b 7x4 0x6 192m) SR: 53.84

dismissalComment.html: Crash! Simmons backs up even before the release, Naved pings the blockhole and bang. The furniture is disturbed. Simmons was trying to drive square on the off side. A very good innings from the youngster.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c Taylor b Gayle 31 (43b 2x4 1x6 60m) SR: 72.09

dismissalComment.html: what a catch! Tossed up on middle and off, Hafeez again goes down and tries the slog-sweep, not timed as well as the previous attempts, ends up slamming it high down towards a very wide long-on, looks like its going for maximum but Taylor times his jump to perfection and pouches it above his head, great stuff and Gayle gets the breakthrough

dismissalText.commentary: Imran Farhat c Samuels b Collymore 58 (72b 5x4 2x6 121m) SR: 80.55

dismissalComment.html: and gone! 43 required off 59 balls and Farhat swings his bat around as if they require 430 off 59 balls - ball clips the top edge and balloons up towards long-off. Samuels moves in from the deep and nicely settles under it.

dismissalText.commentary: Kamran Akmal c †Ramdin b Gayle 23 (20b 4x4 0x6 28m) SR: 115

dismissalComment.html: gone! Tossed up on leg stump, Akmal gets a huge stride forward and goes for the sweep again, ball kisses the gloves and Ramdin takes it neatly, appeals, but Gayle's so confident that he doesnt even look back at the umpire, just breaks out in a smile and walks down towards Ramdin, and behind him Rauf lifts the dreaded finger
